# Example .authinfo file for HuggingFace Browser
#
# Copy this to ~/.authinfo (plain text) or ~/.authinfo.gpg (encrypted)
#
# Format: machine HOST login USERNAME password TOKEN
#
# For HuggingFace API:
machine api-inference.huggingface.co login your-username password hf_YourActualTokenHere

# Alternative format (if you prefer using the main hub):
machine huggingface.co login your-username password hf_YourActualTokenHere

# You can also add other services in the same file:
# machine api.openai.com login apikey password sk-YourOpenAIKeyHere
# machine api.anthropic.com login apikey password sk-ant-YourAnthropicKeyHere

# Notes:
# 1. The 'login' field can be anything (it's not used by the API)
# 2. The 'password' field contains your actual HuggingFace token
# 3. Your token should start with 'hf_'
# 4. Get your token from: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
#
# Security recommendations:
# - Use .authinfo.gpg (encrypted) instead of plain .authinfo
# - Set file permissions: chmod 600 ~/.authinfo
# - Never commit .authinfo to git
# - Add to .gitignore if in a project directory
